com.paymill.models
Class Webhook

java.lang.Object
  com.paymill.models.Webhook

public final class Webhook
extends Object

With webhooks we give you the possibility to react automatically to certain events which happen within our system. A webhook is basically a URL where we send an HTTP POST request to, every time one of the events attached to that webhook is triggered. Alternatively you can define an email address where we send the eventâ€™s information to You can manage your webhooks via the API as explained below or you can use the web interface inside our cockpit.

Since:
3.0.0
